5000|$|Sky cover (/SK) is used {{to report}} the <b>cloud</b> <b>layer</b> amounts and {{the height of the}} cloud base. The tops of the <b>cloud</b> <b>layers</b> can also be included, as can more than one <b>layer</b> of <b>cloud.</b> Heights are in {{hundreds}} of feet above sea level and are three digits. Abbreviations used in this group are [...] "CLR" [...] (clear), [...] "FEW" [...] (few), [...] "SCT" [...] (scattered), [...] "BKN" [...] (broken) and [...] "OVC" [...] (overcast).|$|R
